Process called "test_fft_form_babai_matches_zint_n4" that takes results as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Direct comparison test: drive the same Babai input (f, g, F, G, n=4)
    through the FFT-form shim and verify the result is identical to the
    pure-zint-kernel reference.  Confirms the FFT-form Babai produces
    the same Bezout (F, G) as the exact arithmetic path on inputs that
    fit comfortably inside the precision gate.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    1. Build small f, g (single-limb coefficients).
    2. Build an "initial" F, G by lifting the trivial constant (q, 0)
       lifted via the descent's first-iteration lift pattern.  Use the
       exact same starting (F, G) for both paths.
    3. Path A: call ntru_solve (which dispatches via the new shim).
       Capture the resulting (F, G).
    4. Path B: temporarily force the slow path by passing larger f, g
       and rerun -- this exercises the zint kernel.  The shapes of
       (F, G) coefficients will differ since path B uses a different
       (f, g), so this test compares only path A vs the NTRU invariant
       f*G - g*F = q.  That is, the FFT-form path is verified against
       the algebraic identity rather than a parallel zint run.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    n = 4 test costs <1 ms.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Public test data.
    @End Security_Scope
    T.begin_suite(results, "ntrusolve: FFT-form Babai NTRU invariant at n=4")
    Let arena be Arena.arena_create(67108864)
    Let n be 4
    Let q be 12289

    Let f_int be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, n multiplied by 2)
    Let g_int be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, n multiplied by 2)
    Memory.memory_set_int16(f_int, 0, 3)
    Memory.memory_set_int16(f_int, 2, 1)
    Memory.memory_set_int16(f_int, 4, 0 minus 2)
    Memory.memory_set_int16(f_int, 6, 1)
    Memory.memory_set_int16(g_int, 0, 2)
    Memory.memory_set_int16(g_int, 2, 0 minus 1)
    Memory.memory_set_int16(g_int, 4, 1)
    Memory.memory_set_int16(g_int, 6, 0 minus 1)

    Let F_out be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, n multiplied by 2)
    Let G_out be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, n multiplied by 2)
    Let rc be NS.ntru_solve(arena, f_int, g_int, n, F_out, G_out)
    T.assert_equal(results, "ntru_solve via FFT-form shim rc == 1", rc, 1)

    Note: NTRU invariant f*G - g*F = q in K_n.
    Let f_p be ZP.zint_poly_from_int_array(arena, f_int, n, 2)
    Let g_p be ZP.zint_poly_from_int_array(arena, g_int, n, 2)
    Let F_p be ZP.zint_poly_from_int_array(arena, F_out, n, 2)
    Let G_p be ZP.zint_poly_from_int_array(arena, G_out, n, 2)
    Let fG be ZP.zint_poly_mul(arena, f_p, G_p, n)
    Let gF be ZP.zint_poly_mul(arena, g_p, F_p, n)
    Let delta be ZP.zint_poly_sub(arena, fG, gF, n)
    Let d0 be Z.zint_to_int(ZP.zint_poly_get(delta, 0))
    T.assert_equal(results, "FFT-form: (f*G - g*F)[0] = q", d0, q)
    Let i be 1
    While i is less than n:
        Let di be Z.zint_to_int(ZP.zint_poly_get(delta, i))
        T.assert_equal(results, "FFT-form: (f*G - g*F)[i>=1] = 0", di, 0)
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Arena.arena_destroy(arena)
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "test_fft_form_babai_direct_call_n8" that takes results as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Direct kernel test: call ntrusolve_fft_babai_reduce_fft_form
    directly with pre-FFT'd inputs and verify that one Babai
    iteration drives a manufactured (F, G) toward zero relative to
    (f, g).  This bypasses ntru_solve so the FFT-form kernel is
    exercised in isolation.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    1. Build small f, g zint polynomials of size n=8.
    2. Build F = c*f, G = c*g for an integer constant c=5.  By
       construction the Babai-quotient k should round to c on this
       input, leaving F - k*f = 0 and G - k*g = 0.
    3. Forward-FFT all four into separate buffers at baseline_used=2.
    4. Compute f_conj_fft, g_conj_fft, denom_fft = |f|^2 + |g|^2.
    5. Call ntrusolve_fft_babai_reduce_fft_form for max_iter=8.
    6. Inverse-FFT F_fft, G_fft and round to integers.  Expect every
       coefficient to be 0 (with fp53 round-off, "0" is checked via
       |coef| <= small tolerance).
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    n = 8 test costs <1 ms.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Public test data.
    @End Security_Scope
    T.begin_suite(results, "ntrusolve: FFT-form Babai direct call F=c*f drives to 0")
    Let arena be Arena.arena_create(67108864)
    Let n be 8

    Let f_p be ZP.zint_poly_create(arena, n, 2)
    Let g_p be ZP.zint_poly_create(arena, n, 2)
    Let F_p be ZP.zint_poly_create(arena, n, 2)
    Let G_p be ZP.zint_poly_create(arena, n, 2)

    Note: Build f, g with simple small coefficients.
    Let f_coeffs be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, n multiplied by 8)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(f_coeffs, 0, 3)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(f_coeffs, 8, 1)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(f_coeffs, 16, 0 minus 2)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(f_coeffs, 24, 1)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(f_coeffs, 32, 0)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(f_coeffs, 40, 1)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(f_coeffs, 48, 0 minus 1)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(f_coeffs, 56, 2)

    Let g_coeffs be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, n multiplied by 8)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(g_coeffs, 0, 1)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(g_coeffs, 8, 0 minus 1)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(g_coeffs, 16, 2)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(g_coeffs, 24, 1)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(g_coeffs, 32, 0 minus 1)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(g_coeffs, 40, 0)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(g_coeffs, 48, 1)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(g_coeffs, 56, 0 minus 2)

    Let c be 5
    Let pi be 0
    While pi is less than n:
        Let fv be Memory.memory_get_int64(f_coeffs, pi multiplied by 8)
        Let gv be Memory.memory_get_int64(g_coeffs, pi multiplied by 8)
        Let fz be Z.zint_from_int(arena, fv)
        Let gz be Z.zint_from_int(arena, gv)
        Let Fz be Z.zint_from_int(arena, c multiplied by fv)
        Let Gz be Z.zint_from_int(arena, c multiplied by gv)
        ZP.zint_poly_set(f_p, pi, fz)
        ZP.zint_poly_set(g_p, pi, gz)
        ZP.zint_poly_set(F_p, pi, Fz)
        ZP.zint_poly_set(G_p, pi, Gz)
        Set pi to pi plus 1
    End While

    Note: Forward FFT all four at baseline_used = 2.
    Let buf_bytes be n multiplied by 16
    Let f_fft be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, buf_bytes)
    Let g_fft be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, buf_bytes)
    Let F_fft be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, buf_bytes)
    Let G_fft be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, buf_bytes)
    Let f_conj_fft be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, buf_bytes)
    Let g_conj_fft be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, buf_bytes)
    Let denom_fft be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, buf_bytes)
    ZP.zint_poly_to_fft(arena, f_p, n, f_fft, 2)
    ZP.zint_poly_to_fft(arena, g_p, n, g_fft, 2)
    ZP.zint_poly_to_fft(arena, F_p, n, F_fft, 2)
    ZP.zint_poly_to_fft(arena, G_p, n, G_fft, 2)
    FFT.fft_conj(f_fft, f_conj_fft, n)
    FFT.fft_conj(g_fft, g_conj_fft, n)

    Note: denom = |f|^2 + |g|^2.
    Let zero_v be FP.fp_zero()
    Let si be 0
    While si is less than n:
        Let fr be FFT.fft_get_real(f_fft, si)
        Let fi be FFT.fft_get_imag(f_fft, si)
        Let gr be FFT.fft_get_real(g_fft, si)
        Let gi be FFT.fft_get_imag(g_fft, si)
        Let fr2 be FP.fp_mul(fr, fr)
        Let fi2 be FP.fp_mul(fi, fi)
        Let gr2 be FP.fp_mul(gr, gr)
        Let gi2 be FP.fp_mul(gi, gi)
        Let fmag be FP.fp_add(fr2, fi2)
        Let gmag be FP.fp_add(gr2, gi2)
        Let dmag be FP.fp_add(fmag, gmag)
        FFT.fft_set_real(denom_fft, si, dmag)
        FFT.fft_set_imag(denom_fft, si, zero_v)
        Set si to si plus 1
    End While

    Note: Call the FFT-form kernel directly.
    Let iter_count be NS.ntrusolve_fft_babai_reduce_fft_form(arena, f_fft, g_fft, F_fft, G_fft, f_conj_fft, g_conj_fft, denom_fft, n, 8)
    T.assert_greater_than(results, "FFT-form kernel returned >= 0 iterations", iter_count plus 1, 0)

    Note: Inverse-FFT F_fft, G_fft and check coefficients are zero.
    FFT.fft_inverse(arena, F_fft, n)
    FFT.fft_inverse(arena, G_fft, n)
    Let ci be 0
    While ci is less than n:
        Let Fr be FFT.fft_get_real(F_fft, ci)
        Let Gr be FFT.fft_get_real(G_fft, ci)
        Let F_int be FP.fp_to_int_round(Fr)
        Let G_int be FP.fp_to_int_round(Gr)
        T.assert_equal(results, "F[i] reduced to 0", F_int, 0)
        T.assert_equal(results, "G[i] reduced to 0", G_int, 0)
        Set ci to ci plus 1
    End While

    Arena.arena_destroy(arena)
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "test_fft_form_babai_precision_fallback" that takes results as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Precision-rejection fallback test: drive ntru_solve with a small
    f, g but a constructed (F, G) whose coefficients exceed the
    fp53 precision gate.  The shim must reject the FFT path and fall
    through to the exact zint kernel, still producing a correct
    Bezout.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Since the shim is called only inside ntru_solve_zint and not
    directly with arbitrary (F, G), this test exercises the shim via
    ntru_solve_zint on inputs where the descent's lift produces large
    F, G coefficients.  Choose f, g with non-trivial magnitude so the
    lifted F, G after the n/2 -> n descent step has bit length >50
    bits at the top level.  The test runs ntru_solve and checks the
    NTRU invariant; success means the fallback path produced a valid
    Bezout.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    n = 32 with mid-magnitude coefficients exercises both paths.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Public test data.
    @End Security_Scope
    T.begin_suite(results, "ntrusolve: FFT-form shim with precision fallback at n=32")
    Let arena be Arena.arena_create(134217728)
    Let n be 32
    Let q be 12289

    Let f_int be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, n multiplied by 2)
    Let g_int be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, n multiplied by 2)
    Memory.memory_zero(f_int, n multiplied by 2)
    Memory.memory_zero(g_int, n multiplied by 2)
    Memory.memory_set_int16(f_int, 0, 5)
    Memory.memory_set_int16(f_int, 2, 0 minus 3)
    Memory.memory_set_int16(f_int, 4, 2)
    Memory.memory_set_int16(f_int, 8, 1)
    Memory.memory_set_int16(f_int, 16, 0 minus 1)
    Memory.memory_set_int16(g_int, 0, 0 minus 2)
    Memory.memory_set_int16(g_int, 2, 4)
    Memory.memory_set_int16(g_int, 6, 1)
    Memory.memory_set_int16(g_int, 12, 0 minus 1)
    Memory.memory_set_int16(g_int, 20, 1)

    Let F_out be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, n multiplied by 2)
    Let G_out be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, n multiplied by 2)
    Let rc be NS.ntru_solve(arena, f_int, g_int, n, F_out, G_out)
    T.assert_equal(results, "ntru_solve rc == 1 (mixed FFT/zint paths)", rc, 1)

    Let f_p be ZP.zint_poly_from_int_array(arena, f_int, n, 2)
    Let g_p be ZP.zint_poly_from_int_array(arena, g_int, n, 2)
    Let F_p be ZP.zint_poly_from_int_array(arena, F_out, n, 2)
    Let G_p be ZP.zint_poly_from_int_array(arena, G_out, n, 2)
    Let fG be ZP.zint_poly_mul(arena, f_p, G_p, n)
    Let gF be ZP.zint_poly_mul(arena, g_p, F_p, n)
    Let delta be ZP.zint_poly_sub(arena, fG, gF, n)
    Let d0 be Z.zint_to_int(ZP.zint_poly_get(delta, 0))
    T.assert_equal(results, "fallback: (f*G - g*F)[0] = q", d0, q)
    Let i be 1
    While i is less than n:
        Let di be Z.zint_to_int(ZP.zint_poly_get(delta, i))
        T.assert_equal(results, "fallback: (f*G - g*F)[i>=1] = 0", di, 0)
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Arena.arena_destroy(arena)
    Return 1
End Process

